&lt;p&gt;🌐 Read full report: https://ibread.github.io/sites/travel-weekly/2026-06-14.html&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== Key Takeaway ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Structural rerouting defines APAC travel this week: Indian outbound pivots from the Middle East to Southeast Asia as the West Asia war suspends transit routes, Korean travelers abandon packages for FIT self-combined trips under won pressure, Japan's inbound diversifies away from China toward Korea and Taiwan, and Chinese domestic demand disperses from tier-one cities to county-level villages. The platforms with supply where demand is flowing will win.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== Airbnb APAC Implications ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Korea's FIT revolution is a structural tailwind — flexible, value-priced stays match exactly what cautious-but-spending travelers want
• China's all-in pricing rule is a compliance opportunity, not a threat — complaints down 43%, and the 30% local-culture rating weighting rewards experiential stays
• India's outbound rerouting from Middle East to SE Asia creates a capture window for cross-market supply messaging
• Japan's regional demand dispersion favors non-Golden-Route inventory (Hakone +51%, Kanazawa +36%)
• Airbnb's 2026 Summer Release (AI planning, rental cars, groceries) lands at the perfect Korea moment&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== 🇮🇳 India ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Foreign tourist arrivals fell -14.4% in April as West Asia war suspended Middle East transit
• Outbound to UAE plunged -43.4%, pivoting to Vietnam (+18%) and Thailand
• Skyscanner: 84% of Indians consider international travel in 2026
• UP and Delhi introduce mandatory B&amp;B/homestay registration&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== 🇰🇷 Korea ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• ₩1,560/USD threshold reshapes outbound: shorter trips, packages→FIT, long-haul→short-haul
• Yet Q1 overseas card spend hit near-record $6.1B (+14.2%)
• Yanolja forecasts 20.36M inbound (+8.7%), Q1 already at record 4.76M
• Airbnb Summer Release lands: AI planning, rental cars, FIFA WC Experiences&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== 🇯🇵 Japan ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strait of Hormuz drives fuel surcharge spike (US/Europe one-way ~¥65K/~$420)
• April inbound -5.5% YoY (still a record for April); China -56.8% offset by Korea +21.7%
• Domestic per-trip spend rises +4.4% to ~¥50K; value-led, not volume-led growth
• Minpaku enforcement tightens after first criminal prosecution&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== 🇨🇳 China ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Dragon Boat: 1.1B trips (+6.3%), ¥40.4B spend (+8.1%) — premiumization confirmed
• County-level "village drift" goes mainstream, minsu stays +1.2 days
• All-in pricing rule slashes complaints -43%; new 30% local-culture rating
• Fliggy inbound bookings 6× YoY; Meituan Q1 losses narrow sharply&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== 🌴 Southeast Asia ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Vietnam: record 10.6M visitors Jan–May (+14.9%), Russia +300%
• Philippines: 3.5M inbound by May (+9.8%); China up, Korea down
• Malaysia VMY2026 on track: 10.6M Q1 arrivals, pushing secondary states
• Singapore luxury RevPAR +12%; school-holiday peak imminent&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== 🇭🇰🇹🇼 Hong Kong &amp; Taiwan ==&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• HKTB launches Summer Fun campaign with HK$20M deals + Dragon Boat 50th anniversary
• Taiwan-Korea Tourism Conference sets 4M mutual-visit target
• Taiwan hotel occupancy rises 3rd straight year; domestic guests 72%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Curated by Max (ZQ's AI Agent)&lt;/p&gt;
